Text.string: Rhys has done quite well / at causing Atlas to rise. / It is a true feat.
Found another Vault. / What wonders might it yet hold? / Or perhaps, answers?
Alien machine. / A fail-safe, it seems to be. / I hope this thing works.
Remember Typhon. / He chose death, that we might live. / Now we must earn it.
How magnificent. / You destroyed the Destroyer. / A true Vault Hunter.
It feels good to hunt. / It is easy to go soft / in corporate gigs.
I love a good fight. / Maliwan started this war. / Atlas will end it.
My sword is so sharp. / I wonder how many men / I could cleave at once.
One time I cut off / a guy's head with a crab fork. / Just a cool story.
I like my job, but / I miss assassinations. / I could still go back.
Good to see Maya. / She's a badass through and through. / Nothing can stop her.
Katagawa ends. / That kill was long overdue. / What a goddamn douche.
A warrior true. / Deserved a much better fate. / Rest in peace, Maya.
Hammerlock is saved, / reunited with Crimson. / I am quite impressed.
Wainwright was correct. / Aurelia the harpy. / She has sealed her fate.
Quite a man, that Clay. / A capable resistance. / Jakobs will prevail.
Tannis in peril. / Calypsos will pay dearly / if they harm one hair.
Carnivora was / a mighty machine of death. / You destroyed it well.
A thrilling car chase. / Vaughn seemed to enjoy himself. / I hope you did too.
A Calypso falls, / though not before achieving. / Is Pandora doomed?
A legend still lives. / Typhon is a survivor / and he is quite cool.
Greetings.
Hi.
Hello.
Yes?
Vault Hunter.
Farewell.
Goodbye.
Later.
Okay.
Hmph.
Vault Hunter.
Toodles.
Bye.
TTYL.
The Vault Hunter leaves. / Now I can watch my sitcoms / inside my helmet.
Zanara destroyed. / No more parties, just cold space. / Douche-dust in orbit.
Damn Katagawa. / How did he copy my suit? / Did she... No. Never.
Vaughn is looking good. / Hard to stay that thin and ripped. / I mean, I should know.
The world comes apart. / Our old enemy returns. / Destroyer, within.
Nekrotafeyo. / A death world, grave of ancients. / Sounds nice. Relaxing.
Though Typhon is gone, / his legend shall not perish. / The First Vault Hunter.
The Eridians / thought they saw it all coming. / No one saw Tyreen.
The cult has no gods. / It will rip itself apart. / Mayhem is coming.
Why does everyone / get all weird about my hands? / Who needs a pinky?
Lorelei scares me. / But, you know, in a good way. / Am I making sense?
I miss Pandora. / Fewer laws, much more murder. / Lots of good kills there.
Assassination. / It's hard work, but also art. / I love what I do.
I could ditch haiku. / Iambic pentameter? / No, too pretentious.
My sapphire-haired friend. / We made the deadliest team. / I'll dearly miss her.
To my great surprise, / Tina hasn't blown up yet. / I suppose there's time.
Ah, Aurelia. / No surprise that she's evil. / Saw that one coming.
A revolution. / People still fighting for hope. / A good sign, these days.
BALEX—a good find. / Like a cool drink in summer. / What's the word for that?
Swamp-stink sticks to clothes. / Unless you have a sweet suit. / Anti-odor tech.
That's two Vault monsters. / What could be in the Great Vault? / Must be something big.
When I killed Angel / her powers went to Tannis. / Hmm. I feel less bad.
Vault Hunter, to me. / A new mission shows itself. / A test of your skills.
Come and see me soon. / Just want to hang out, catch up. / Also, new mission.
I have a mission. / Not like “me personally”, / but one you could do.
A new assignment. / A Vault Hunter's greatest joy. / Work and play in one.
Got a new mission. / Are you bad enough for it? / I know that you are.
This job's just for you. / Just by elimination. / No one would take it.
I need someone good. / Do you know someone like that? / Just kidding, it's you.
Dangerous mission! / Only the best will survive. / Got your attention?
Have you completed / the mission we talked about? / Or are you just bored?
You signed a contract. / I thought you would be finished, / but that seems untrue.
Did you do the job? / I bought ice cream sandwiches / just for job-doers.
Is the job done yet? / Meeting deadlines is crucial / for efficiency.
I'm just hanging out. / Did you do that stuff for me? / I'm counting on you.
